Still Breathing

BLAISE BOSTELMANN

the Recycled Pixel

I am an admirer of electrons, and photons. From wishing I had the superpower to harness, to becoming an engineer so that I can harness. It is these particles which excite and inspire me.


I value all the little big things in life. From a climatic page of text in a grand plot, to the short honorary moment of receiving my four year degree. It is these short yet large bursts of energy which propel me to the next.


I seek to learn, to create, and to inspire. From learning about the chemistry of preservation, to creating a jar of preserved lemons, and finally sharing these lemons with family and friends. It is these experiences which I make my path.


I am Blaise Bostelmann, and through the use of electrons and photons I will share all the little big moments of my life, whither it be my learning or creating, I hope the end result will inspire.


E=n⋅joy2
